			<div class="content" id="post-content-2791392">
									

<p>I think you missed a couple important lines here:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Due to these lim­i­ta­tions, trans­port of peo­ple, ob­jects, or an­i­mals into the past is largely out of the ques­tion. How­ever, it is rel­a­tively straight­for­ward to trans­mit dig­i­tal in­for­ma­tion us­ing streams of par­ti­cles and sen­si­tive de­tec­tors.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The <em>point</em> is that the only way to send anything bigger than a few atoms or to run a causality-violating computer is to build some space-opera-grade megastructure ballasted by planetoids and powered by a dyson sphere, or to employ paratech that does extremely rude things to the laws of physics. Sending information, on the other hand, is fairly reasonable in this hypothetical system.</p>

							</div>

								
